    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm looking at some high protein dog food for my lab, he's getting up there in age (about 9). i noticed the protein is pretty high but i'm worried about the fat content and how it affects him long term. what's a good protein to fat ratio for an older lab?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an older Labrador, a balanced approach is best; aim for a food that is high in quality, easily digestible protein but also moderate in fat. Generally, a ratio leaning towards a higher protein and controlled fat content, such as 25-30% protein with a moderate fat level, is suitable. Since he is aging, look for foods that specifically mention \"senior\" formulas to ensure the nutrients are tailored for joint and immune support.",
