      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While 40% protein is quite high, it can be beneficial for older dogs to help counteract age-related muscle loss (sarcopenia). However, 15% fat might be a good level, but always check the quality of the fats—look for healthy sources like omega fatty acids. If switching significantly, transition very slowly over several weeks to prevent digestive upset in your Lab.",
